OL,3,C'Better days will come': Lily on her
OL,4,Cnew life as a quadruple amputee
OL,6,FA 24-year-old woman who became a
OL,7,Fquadruple amputee as a result of
OL,8,Fcontracting sepsis is determined to
OL,9,Frebuild her life and says, "better
OL,10,Fdays will come".
OL,12,FLily McGarry, 24 and from Jersey, was
OL,13,Fstudying medicine at Cardiff
OL,14,FUniversity when she went to A&E with
OL,15,Fflu-like symptoms in January, before
OL,16,Fsuffering two cardiac arrests.
OL,18,FAfter months of being in a coma and
OL,19,Fthen undergoing seven surgeries in
OL,20,Ffive weeks, Lily says she will not
OL,21,Fstop fighting for her future.
