OL,3,C'Better days will come': Lily on her
OL,4,Cnew life as a quadruple amputee
OL,6,FLily says in her darker moments, her
OL,7,Fgratitude towards all those who have
OL,8,Fcared for her and the "countless
OL,9,Fmembers of staff who have worked
OL,10,Ftirelessly to keep me here" keeps her
OL,11,Fgoing.
OL,13,FLily's mother, Jo, says that in the
OL,14,Fpast month, the trajectory of recovery
OL,15,Fhas really accelerated, but it will be
OL,16,Fa long process.
