OL,3,C'Better days will come': Lily on her
OL,4,Cnew life as a quadruple amputee
OL,6,FJo describes: "Day by day she's
OL,7,Fnoticing what she can do, it's still a
OL,8,Fcouple of years of recovery before we
OL,9,Fcan say what her functional level will
OL,10,Fbe.
OL,12,F"You have to bring that strength to
OL,13,FLily. There are days when you wake up
OL,14,Fand think, 'Can I do this again?' but
OL,15,Fyou do - because you have to.
OL,17,F"We were very close to losing her,
OL,18,Fthere's only so much the human body
OL,19,Fcan take - she keeps fighting and she
OL,20,Fkeeps smiling."
